Simple Calculator using HTML, CSS, and JavaScript

Simple Calculator

This simple calculator is a web-based application built using HTML, CSS, and JavaScript. It allows users to perform basic arithmetic operations like addition, subtraction, multiplication, and division with ease.

Features

User-Friendly Interface: The calculator has a clean and intuitive user interface, making it easy for users to perform calculations.

Basic Arithmetic Operations: You can perform addition, subtraction, multiplication, and division using this calculator.

Responsive Design: The calculator is responsive and works well on various screen sizes, including desktop and mobile devices.

How It Works

Number Buttons:     Click on the number buttons to input the numbers you want to perform calculations with.

Operator Buttons:   Click on the operator buttons (+, -, *, /) to select the desired arithmetic operation.

Equals (=) Button:  Press the equals button to see the result of your calculation.

Clear (C) Button:   Use the clear button to reset the calculator for a new calculation.

Technologies Used

1.HTML: The structure and layout of the calculator are created using HTML.

2.CSS: CSS styles are applied to enhance the visual appearance and make the calculator responsive.

3.JavaScript: JavaScript is used to handle user interactions, perform calculations, and display results dynamically.

Try It Out

You can try out this simple calculator by opening the calculator.html file in your web browser.
Feel free to use it for your day-to-day calculations or as a reference for building more advanced calculator applications.

Customization

If you'd like to customize or extend this calculator, you can easily modify the HTML, CSS, and JavaScript code to suit your needs.
It's a great starting point for learning web development and building interactive web applications.

Acknowledgments

This project is created for educational purposes and serves as a basic example of building a calculator using web technologies. 
It can be expanded and improved upon to create more sophisticated calculator applications.

Enjoy using the simple calculator, and happy coding!




